The `storedSource` option has the following syntax in an [index definitions](ref-index-definitions):

```json
{
  "storedSource": true | false | {
    "include" | "exclude": [
      "<field-name>",
      ...
    ]
  }
}
```

The following index examples use the fields in the
`sample_mflix.movies` collection to demonstrate how to configure the
fields to store on MongoDB Search using the `storedSource` option. You can use
[mongosh](mongodb-shell), the Atlas UI Visual Editor, or the Atlas UI JSON Editor to
configure the indexes.***➤ Use the **Select your language** drop-down menu to set the
interface for the procedure on this page.***drivers**Atlas UI:**Atlas UI**Include:**Store SpecifiedThe following example stores only the `title` and
`awards.wins` fields in the documents in the collection.
After you select your preferred configuration method, select
the `movies` collection under the `sample_mflix` database.**Vib:**Visual Editor* Click **Refine Your Index** to configure your
  index.

* In the **Stored Source Fields** section, click
  **Specified**.

* Select `awards.wins` from the dropdown in the
  **Field Name** column and click **Add**.

* Click **Add Field** to specify another field
  to store.

* Select `title` from the dropdown in the
  **Field Name** column and click
  **Add**.

* Click **Save Changes**.**Jsonib:**JSON EditorAppend lines 5 to 10 from the following example to the
index definition to store the specified fields on MongoDB Search. The
example uses the [dot notation](manual/core/document) to specify nested
fields.```json
{
  "mappings": {
    "dynamic": true,
  },
  "storedSource": {
     "include": [
        "title",
        "awards.wins"
     ]
  }
}
```**Exclude:**Exclude SpecifiedThe following example stores all fields except `directors`
and `imdb.rating` in the documents in the collection. After
you select your preferred configuration method, select the
`movies` collection under the `sample_mflix` database.**Vib:**Visual Editor* Click **Refine Your Index** to configure your
  index.

* In the **Stored Source Fields** section, click
  **All Except Specified**.

* Select `directors` from the dropdown in the
  **Field Name** column and click **Add**.

* Click **Add Field** to specify another field
  to exclude.

* Select `imdb.rating` from the dropdown in the
  **Field Name** column and click
  **Add**.

* Click **Save Changes**.**Jsonib:**JSON EditorAppend lines 5 to 10 from the following example to the
index definition to exclude the specified fields. The example uses
the [dot notation](manual/core/document)
to specify nested fields.```json
{
  "mappings": {
    "dynamic": true,
  },
  "storedSource": {
    "exclude": [
      "directors",
      "imdb.rating"
    ]
  }
}
```**Storeall:**Store All FieldsThe following example stores all the fields in the documents
in the collection. After you select your preferred
configuration method, select the `movies` collection under
the `sample_mflix` database.**Vib:**Visual Editor* Click **Refine Your Index** to configure your
  index.

* In the **Stored Source Fields** section, click
  **All**.

* Click **Save Changes**.**Jsonib:**JSON EditorAppend line 5 from the following example to the index
definition to store all of the fields.```json
{
  "mappings": {
    "dynamic": true,
  },
  "storedSource": true,
}
```**Shell:**MongoDB Shell**Include:**Store SpecifiedThe following example for the `sample_mflix.movies`
namespace stores only the `title` and `awards.wins`
fields in the documents on `mongot`:```javascript
db.movies.createSearchIndex(
   "default",
   "definition": {
      "mappings": {
         "dynamic": true,
      },
      "storedSource": {
        "include": [
           "title",
           "awards.wins"
        ]
     }
   }
)
```**Exclude:**Exclude SpecifiedThe following example for the `sample_mflix.movies`
namespace stores all fields except `directors` and
`imdb.rating` in the documents.```javascript
db.movies.createSearchIndex(
   "default",
   "definition": {
     "mappings": {
       "dynamic": true,
     },
     "storedSource": {
       "exclude": [
         "directors",
         "imdb.rating"
       ]
     }
   }
)
```**Storeall:**Store All FieldsThe following example for the `sample_mflix.movies`
namespace stores all the fields in the documents
in the collection.```javascript
db.movies.createSearchIndex(
   "default",
   "definition": {
     "mappings": {
       "dynamic": true,
     },
     "storedSource": true,
   }
)
```
